in Windows, just run build.bat in CMD. The visual studio solution, 'descriptors.sln', will be generated in the .\build

in Linux
> ./build.sh [Debug|Release]
> cd [Debug|Release]
> make; make install

OPTIONS
======
-DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=where_to_install               specify the dir to install the library
-DBABEL_INCLUDE_DIR=where_openbabel_include           specify where to find <openbabel/xx.h>
-DBABEL_LIB_DIR=where_openbabel.so                    specify where to find openbabel.dll or libopenbabel.so
-DBUILD_SHARED=ON                                     enable shared build
-DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug|Release					  specify Debug or Release mode


